data.content:
noun
plural -ups
chiefly US
[count] :an exercise or set of exercises done to prepare for a sport or other activity
She did a five-minute warmup before running. - often plural
He injured himself during warmups.
[count] :something done before something else to prepare an audience, a group, etc., for the next thing - usually singular
This presentation is just a warmup for the big session tomorrow.
Dinner is just a warmup. You should see what we're having for dessert!
He's just the warmup act.
warmups [plural] :comfortable clothing worn by athletes while they are preparing for competition - usually plural
The race was about to start, so the runners removed their warmups. - called also warmup suit, - see also warm up at 2warm
